\pi(C,d)=\frac{C}{d}
(\pi)'=\left(\frac{C}{d}\right)
\frac{\partial \pi}{\partial C}
\frac{\partial \pi}{\partial C}=\frac{1}{d}\cdot\frac{\partial}{\partial C}(C)=\frac{1}{d}\cdot1=\frac{1}{d}
\frac{\partial \pi}{\partial d}=C\frac{\partial}{\partial d}\left(\frac{1}{d}\right)=C\cdot\frac{-1}{d^2}=-\frac{C}{d^2}
